Contribution Guidelines :

Thank you for your interest in contributing to the Body Mass Index Calculator Android Studio project!

Ways to Contribute

There are many ways to contribute to this project, including but not limited to:

Finding and reporting bugs
Suggesting and implementing new features
Improving documentation and code comments
Fixing code issues or enhancing code quality
Translating the app into different languages
Creating tutorials or guides on how to use the app.

Getting Started

To get started, fork the repository and create a new  branch for your changes. Then,  make your  changes and test them 
thoroughly to ensure that they work correctly. Once you're happy with your changes, create a pull request with a clear 
description of the changes you've made.

Code Style:
Please follow the existing code style when making changes to the project. If you're unsure about the style, please refer
to the Android Studio documentation or consult with the project maintainers.

Issue Tracking:
If you find a bug or would like to suggest a new feature, please open an issue on GitHub. Please include a clear description
of the issue or feature request, along with any relevant screenshots or error messages.

Code of Conduct:
This project follows the Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct. Please read the full text here before contributing.
